  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDataDelegate<BsTestNatural,com.poesys.db.dto.TestNatural,com.poesys.db.pk.NaturalPrimaryKey>

    public class TestNaturalDelegate
extends AbstractDataDelegate<BsTestNatural,com.poesys.db.dto.TestNatural,com.poesys.db.pk.NaturalPrimaryKey>
    Tests the connection-related methods on the AbstractDataDelegate using the TestNatural DTO class. This delegate simply implements query, insert, update, and delete methods. This class provides a reference implementation for a data-oriented business delegate. Each data-related method is a single, complete transaction that gets a connection, executes the required operation, and handles any exceptions by embedding them in a DelegateException.
    Author:
    Robert J. Muller

      • wrapData

        protected BsTestNatural wrapData(com.poesys.db.dto.TestNatural dto)
        Description copied from class: AbstractDataDelegate

        Wrap a Data Access Data Transfer Object (DTO) inside a Business DTO. This abstract method lets you call the appropriate constructor on the business DTO as part of the concrete implementation. Here is an example implementation using TestNatural and returning BsTestNatural: 

         
 @Override
 BsTestNatural wrapData(TestNatural dto) {
   return new BsTestNatural(dto);
 }
        Specified by:
        wrapData in class AbstractDataDelegate<BsTestNatural,com.poesys.db.dto.TestNatural,com.poesys.db.pk.NaturalPrimaryKey>
        Parameters:
        dto - the data access DTO
        Returns:
        the business DTO
